olive oil
3 potato
1 white turnip
1 onion
1 packet flaked almonds
1 cucumber
½ packet paneer cheese
2 clove garlic
1 packet Mango Chilli Sauce
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
½ sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
Cut the potato and white turnip into bite-sized
chunks. Slice the red onion into wedges. Place
the veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive
oil, sprinkle with the Mumbai spice blend, season
with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly,
then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes. In the last
2-3 minutes of cook time, add the flaked almonds
to one side of the tray and roast until golden. Set
the veggies aside to cool slightly.

Thinly slice the cucumber into rounds. Cut the
paneer cheese (see ingredients) into 2cm chunks.
Finely chop the garlic.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil and the garlic over a medium-high heat. Cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Transfer to a small bowl. Add the Greek-style yoghurt to the garlic oil mixture and combine. Season to taste and set aside.

In a medium bowl, combine the paneer, mild North Indian spice blend (see ingredients) and a drizzle of olive oil. When veggies have 5 minutes cook time remaining, return the frying pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the paneer, tossing, until golden, 4 minutes. Remove the pan from the heat, then add the mango chilli sauce and a splash of water, tossing the paneer to coat.

In a large bowl, combine the roasted veggies, the
cucumber, salad leaves, a drizzle of white wine
vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

Divide the Mumbai potato toss between bowls. Top with the mango chilli paneer and toasted almonds. Spoon over any remaining glaze from the pan and serve with the garlic yoghurt.